00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:30,740
Amazon has nothing to do with the fulfillment of those orders, and the process looks largely

23
00:01:30,740 --> 00:01:33,680
the same as with any other e-commerce company.

24
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:39,280
What's different is how the other three-quarters of Amazon packages in the US get to you—the

25
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:42,000
ones that are fulfilled directly by Amazon.

26
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,720
The path that these take depends first on how big the package is.

27
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:52,160
You see, Amazon's fulfillment centers are more or less split into three categories—small

28
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:55,600
